subSubSection.paragraph:
Male.
Basal apodeme relatively short for genus, tongue-like (
Figs 4–5
); in distal section with ventral folds that appear to connect to penile sclerites. Endomere without distal extensions, and with proximal extensions rather stout. Penile sclerites barely overlapping with endomere. No setae or sensilla visible on endomere or near base of penis in examined specimens. Parameres with characteristic bend at about midway, overlapping distally; 
pst1–2
sensilla.
